WHAT IS IT?
-----------

  'GridBlock' is a Workbench game where you try to 'unlock' all
4 corners of a 7 by 7 spaces game board. To do this, you have to
move horizontal and vertical bars, so the empty space is moved
to each corner of the board... in other words, it is a different
twist on the usual "sliding-tiles" puzzle.

  What complicates the game a little is that each of the 24 bars
occupy 2 spaces. A bar can only move in the directions it
indicates (I.E.: A horizontal bar can move horizontally and a
vertical bar can move vertically)... if, of course, that bar is
located next to the empty space.

  When you move bars so that the empty space is located at a
corner space of the game board, the border of that corner will
"blow-up" and the corner will be unlocked.

  In GridBlock there are many puzzles to resolve, some are easy
and some are more trickier. As usual, the goal is to try to
complete each puzzle in the least amount of moves possible.

  Have fun!

